description: The adventure of the robot whose mind has been stolen concludes! In a desperate attempt to retrieve his stolen memory bank, Witlock and his team of Trouble Shooters attempt to stop the launch of a manned rocket from a New Mexico spaceport. To reach the rocket, Witlock must battle heavily-armored aerobots as well as his own faulty circuits, racing against time before he forgets all about the memory bank he's been tracking. Or...Witlock who? DOUBLE MAGNET began as an adventure tale, but evolves into a devastating mystery with a genuinely shocking conclusion.
name: The Memory Conflict

description: The adventure of the robot whose mind has been stolen continues! While the mercenary Ernest Smite and a vindictive robot scientist prepare Witlock's missing memory bank for a fiendish operation, our hero receives a tantalizing transmission from the mysterious Mr. Vagor... a message that reveals crucial clues about the theft of his data storage unit. But is Vagor a friend or foe? And what's his connection to Eileen Myles, the scientist who engineered Witlock's artificial intelligence?
name: A Trip to the Moon

description: The adventures of the robot whose mind has been stolen continue! Following his battle with Doctor Chambers in Las Vegas, Witlock discovers his memory bank has been stolen by a trio of masked bandits known as the Faceless Goons. While Witlock's team, the Trouble Shooters, plans its next move, the Faceless Goons deliver the memory bank to a pious mercenary named Ernest. Before the intrepid robot can give chase, he must first confront Sea-Konk, an aquatic sanitation robot who thinks Witlock is the scum of the reservoir!
name: The Murky Depths

description: A robot adventurer who relies on his brain rather than his mechanized brawn struggles to save his own "life" when his high-powered brain is stolen. He was designed to be the U.S. Government's very own toy soldier, but Witlock the Robot asserted his independence instead, turning his highly developed brain towards adventures of his own choosing. But what happens when that brain is stolen, and the world's smartest robot gets, well, stupid? You've got trouble, friend... TROUBLE MAGNET, that is. Written by Ryder Windham (Star Wars: Droids), with art and covers by Kilian Plunkett (UNKNOWN SOLDIER), the 4-issue TROUBLE MAGNET miniseries follows Witlock's adventures as the robot who always relied more on his artificial brain than his brawn discovers that brawn is all he has left. Someone's hijacked Witlock's brainpower, and his memories along with it, and if the increasingly dimwitted robot and his tech-proficient friends can't retrieve them soon, the loss will become permanent. Embarking on a dizzying journey from the bright lights of Las Vegas to the dark side of the Moon, only double-crossing mercenaries and a secret conspiracy stand between Witlock and his missing mind...
name: Saving the Galaxy

description:
SPOILER WARNING: Click here to reveal hidden content.
In this issue we see as Kal - El crawls out of his birthing Matrix on his own. Instead of being picked up by the Kents however, he is run over by a mna who is frightened at first, but sees that the child is absolutely fine. Calling him a miracle baby , the man drops him off at a local orphanage. 
  Not too long from that a young couple named the Sudermans adopt young Kal, and rename him Dale Suderman. Yet fate has other plans than to let this trio become a nuclear family, and soon little Dales father passes away. 
   Not too many years after that, while Dale is still just a toddler, he and his mommy are searching for her keys.  seeing them behind a large dresser, little Dale picks it up, and then flies the keys over to his mother. 
This display of his Kryptonian abilities scares his mother, and as she reels back in horror, she falls down the steps to her death.  This causes Dale to suppress memories of his powers and for the next 10  years, he goes through life a bitter and withdrawn kid. 
   When he is a teen, and in therapy, Dale Suderman is passing by a playground where the kids are playing basketball. He joins in and finds that he has skill in the game. Loving to play, he uses his skill to take him through college, than the pros, and then to superstardom. Not just in basketball, but in all major sports. 
   Through his fame he becomes a buisnessman, yet when he moves to Metropolis and beats out the local buisnessman Lex Luthor for a permit to build a new sports arena, he makes himself an enemy.

"Bite Plight": it's tooth or consequences for Jughead when the tooth fairy undervalues his tooth. Meanwhile, Archie is gaga over the fetching fairy while Betty takes a shine to her hunky supervisor! We promise you, this is one story you'll love to sink your teeth into!"Egology": Everything you always wanted to know about big egos... straight from that most vain and conceited of wise guys, Reggie!
name: Bite Plight!

description: The Mighty Avengers are poised to join the Siege on Asgard, but first they have some pretty big issues to resolve. THOR vs. the MIGHTY AVENGERS! LOKI revealed! Someone's off the team?! The most insane thing HANK PYM will ever do (and for Hank Pym, that's saying a lot)! All this and more!
name: Pre-Siege Mentality

description: Beginning an epic, action-packed arc featuring the debut of an-all new, all different Deathlok. Killer cyborgs have come from the future to kill the heroes of today, while Wolverine embarks on an international pub crawl with a certain recently reborn Sentinel of Liberty. Beer and bullest galore!
name: Tomorrow Dies Today, Part 1

description: STARK: DISSASSEMBLED comes to it's conclusion. The Ghost vs. Maria Hill and Pepper Potts, alone inside an empty middle school! Tony Stark and Dr.Strange vs. the end of the world, alone inside the recesses of Tony's once-great mind! After what as well have been the entirety of the Marvel Universe coming together to help get Iron Man back on his feet, can Tony himself run the last mile alone? What's left of a man after you take him apart?
name: Stark: Disassembled, Conclusion

description: It's an all out super hero throw-down! Captain America and the Avengers face off-as the dreaded Red Skull plots universal mayhem! How will Fury's death squad cope with the legend and his son? The world we know it is on the line! Join superstars MARK MILLAR and CARLOS PACHECO for the nex mind blowing chapter!
name: The Next Generation, Part 5

description:
Hope Summers could be the much-heralded "messiah" who will save mutantkind from extinction...or she could just be some poor kid, caught in the wrong place at the wrong times(s). Either way, since her infancy she's been raised by mutant soldier Cable in a hostile dying future Earth -- and she's had to learn some hard lessons along the way. Now, Duane Swierczynski and Steve Dillon bring you four thrilling, untold tales from Hope's future past as she grapples with vicious snipers, robot pack wolves, mutant rats, and even Cable himself. This is the place to start if you want to know what the X-Men's future "messiah" is made of.

Collects the 3-part "A Girl Called Hope" back-story from Psylocke V2009 #1, Dark X-Men V2010 #1 and X-Men Legacy V2008 #230, and adds the final chapter to that story, leading into Second Coming.
name: A Girl Called Hope

description: If a few super heroes survived the Ultimatum -- who is left to become the next superhero team to be reckoned with? The NEW Ultimates! With Thor gone, Loki takes his revenge unleashing the worst of Asgard on Earth. Iron Man must gather the heroes together for their biggest Ultimates adventure yet. But who has made the final cut? And who can't be trusted? The Ultimates face evil once again, and you'll never guess the new enemies they'll find...or shall we say old friends? Superstar creators JEPH LOEB and FRANK CHO (in his Ultimate Comics debut!) bring you the new face of the Ultimate line in NEW ULTIMATES: THOR REBORN!
name: Thor Reborn, Chapter 1

description: Finn, the bearer of the Glacier Stone, and Glori, the bearer of the Ember Stone, have to overcome their differences to stop a fanatic cult group of remaking the world with the Pandora´s Box.
name: Part 1

description: The search for the source of the black market magics takes Cinderella and Aladdin to the Fables homeland of Ultima Thule where the fall of the Adversary's Empire has led to a bloody revolution. Back in Fabletown, Crispin Cordwainer's new shoe designs inspire a threat from Sheriff Beast.
name: Part Five: Cold Wars
